      "content": "I understand your concern regarding the skewed flagging metrics from specific demographics and zip codes. A recalibration update aiming to mitigate this bias should generally improve the fairness and precision of our fraud detection. However, we must carefully test the new sensitivity thresholds to ensure that reducing bias doesn't inadvertently decrease overall detection accuracy against actual fraudulent patterns. I recommend a phased rollout with rigorous back-testing against historical validated fraud cases.",
